&gt; &gt; &gt; see the
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; patch.  Could you perhaps include a small test case as inline text?
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;    David Saff
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; On Tue, Dec 30, 2008 at 10:27 AM, tuomaskarkkainenri &lt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; tuomaskarkkainenri@&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;   I participate in JDave (http://jdave.org). A BDD framework
&gt; for Java
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; that takes advantage of JUnit for example for Eclipse integration.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; We have tests in non-static inner classes of our test classes.
&gt; These
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; run wonderfully using the @RunWith annotation and our own runner.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; however, for individual tests, this doesn&#39;t work. What I would
&gt; like
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; to do is that AllDefaultPossibilitiesBuilder would check
&gt; whether or
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; not the test class is a non static member class. if it is, then I
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; would grab the runner of the declaring class instead.
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; I made a patch implementing this. I will try to attach it.
